    "recap_headline": "Murray State University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "ST. CHARLES, Mo.\n- Murray State baseball was unable to overcome a dominant pitching performance from Lindenwood on Friday afternoon, falling 4-0 in the opening game of a three-game weekend set at Lou Brock Sports Complex.\nThe Racers (11-7) struggled to find a rhythm at the plate, managing just three hits on the day. After\nKristofer Hokenson\nrecorded a single in the first inning, the Lindenwood (9-9) pitching staff took command, retiring 20 consecutive Murray State batters.\nThe drought lasted until the eighth inning when\nDaylan Pena\nbroke the streak with a single.\nLuke Mistone\nadded the Racers' third and final hit of the contest in the ninth, but the rally stopped there.\nOn the mound,\nNic Schutte\n(2-2) took the loss for Murray State. Schutte logged 4.0 innings and allowed four runs, three of them earned. He struggled with command at times, hitting three batters to tie his season high.\nJackson Ugo\nprovided a bright spot for the Racers out of the bullpen. Ugo tossed 4.0 scoreless innings of relief, surrendering just two hits while striking out four. It marked the best outing of the season for Ugo.\nMurray State will look to even the series tomorrow in game two. First pitch is scheduled for 1 p.m. CST."
